Printventory 2.1 Changelog

✨ New Features & UI Additions

Model Previews: Added fully featured model previews, including dedicated support for 3MF files.

Theme Customization: You can now customize Model Color and Lighting directly within your Theme settings.

Expanded Modals: Added a Full Screen toggle for the DeDup and Tagging modals to give you more workspace.

List View Sorting: Added a sortable header to the List View for easier file management.

Click Menu: Introduced a new click menu system (greatly improving usability, especially in Docker/Server modes).

🚀 Performance Improvements

Faster Scanning: Greatly improved initial scanning performance during the "Gather Files" phase.

Optimized Grid Rendering: Implemented lazy loading for the grid view, significantly smoothing out scrolling and overall performance.

Memory Management: Resolved an issue with the thumbnail memory cache to keep the application running efficiently.

🐳 Docker & Server Mode Enhancements

UI/Input Fixes: Resolved numerous issues with dialog inputs, notes fields, and right-click context menus specific to Docker/Server environments.

Background Tasks: Fixed Docker hash background generation to ensure smooth operation.

🛠️ General Improvements & Bug Fixes

DeDup Handling: Improved how zipped models are handled and processed within the DeDup tool.

File Management: Unselecting a file type will now successfully purge those models from the view.

Filtering & Parsing: Fixed issues with the Parent Directory filter, STL Home Directory parsing, and filtering selected files.

Stability: Fixed a critical bug that caused the application to hang during rendering.

UI Sync: Fixed an issue where the UI would not properly refresh after deleting a file.

General Polish: Various minor UI tweaks, Performance Menu fixes, and under-the-hood bug fixes for a more stable release.
